  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In this randomized-controlled, cross-over trial the investigators test the effect of
      long-term oxygen therapy (&gt; 16h/day) given for 5 weeks with a wash-out period between phases
      of 2 weeks on exercise performance and quality of life and many physiological parameters in
      patients with pulmonary arterial and chronic thromboembolic pulmonary hypertension.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
